caption: Love this place due to covid I have never ate at the restaurant so I can't comment much on the service or the place but food is great!
Fantastic wings
So good. Used a Groupon to get a meal for two that could feed 4 easily. The crust of the chicken is fantastic.
Amazing fried chicken. My go-to is an order of wings the spicy and soy garlic are both delicious.
Very nice
Good spicy drums and wings will be back.
Definitely a regular customer!
Terrible service on Super Bowl Sunday. Waiting still for an order that is over an hour late. Over 30 people waiting on their to go orders.

I am so mad at myself that I didn’t try them sooner. A friend told me to try “Crisp” because in her opinion, they’re better than Bonchon. Well that’s a LIE! These are the best wings I’ve ever tasted, I’m addicted! Thank you Bonchon for the best soy garlic wings ever!!!
ordered soy sauce chicken with coleslaw. the chicken was so good 👍 but didn't get a side dish. ☹️

Good food, great chefs and fantastic bar staff.  Kimchi is $3.50 though. Small dish. Bit of a robbery considering its a BonChon.  Could do w/ implementing a industry special and including Kimchi at no extra cost

I love BonChon, and this one on Division Street is great. Friendly staff, very clean modern casual interior, and fast service. Not to mention the soy garlic wings are so good...I am addicted. And they have some of the best onion rings in town. If you're looking for tasty Korean fried chicken, BonChon is a great option. They also have fun fusion dishes if ur not in the mood for wings.👍
Love the spicy chicken!! wanted to try their Cesar salad, big mistake!! The lettuce clearly was not washed, as you could see dirt.

Ordered ahead online. It was ready with 5 min of the estimated time. Good price for the amount of food you get. I was happy with all the dishes. We got the fried rice, japchae, bull dak and some fried chicken. FYI, the bull dak was pretty spicy. Had to eat it with plenty of rice and I'm into spicy stuff.
The fried chicken tastes terrific!

Seafood fried rice !! Live for it , amazing . Wings are good too - get the mixed one so you can taste different flavors . Only thing is you will know from the taste that they sue bad quality oil for frying and cooking - keeps your stomach troubled for the rest of the day but nothing too uncomfortable or I wouldn’t be ordering from here so regularly lol. Take out is better than eating inside - nothing great about restaurant decor.
Food was tasty and large portions for the price!! Staff was awesome and a large selection of everything. Love Korean food and this did not disappoint! Great experience.

The food was delicious, service was ok but overall experience was cold.  We went on a more chilly day, on division most of the other restaurants had their dining umbrellas out because its a tree lined street and heat lamps due to the weather change.  Bonchon only had table and chairs available but keep the heat lamps and umbrellas in the dining room in eyeyesight of street views.  Not sure of the reason why but we went because if a Groupon and drove from Hyde Park.  Because of the distance I couldn't carry out because I wanted to taste it fresh and have a real Bonchon experience.  I will say the food was wonderful.  We had a 12pc dinner special with half spicy, half soy wings.  They starter was some very tasty & crunchy fries that were cooked perfectly.  The wait was not long at all so our chicken, fried rice, cole slaw and picked radishes came out pretty quickly.  The chicken was also cooked perfectly with the right amount of crisp on the outside and super moist on the inside. Very flavorful and great sauce.  The spicy was no joke for my palette but soo good.  I was able to eat 2 pieces with the cole slaw to help with the heat.  I would return but not to this location. Luckily we have one closer in China Town that ill visit.  The food was delicious and worth 7 stars, but the experience with our new normal of dining outdoors due to COVID and trying to support businesses felt like a slap on the hand.  I would say don't offer outdoor seating if you don't want to fully commit. Just my two cents.
Good place for delicious korean food. stopped in on a monday i think. there was quick, helpful, and friendly service. this place has a good atmosphere. menu is like a place in miami i enjoyed
Very slow service.

Best fried chicken in town! They packed the meal very nice. The fried chicken came in large portion with lots of side dishes. And Emily, the server is very nice and friendly. Will continue ordering from them.
Chicken katsu was very dry. Coleslaw tasted terrible. Chicken strips were ok.  Overall, sub average and waste of $
Delicious chicken...! I enjoy the food..
This spot is fantastic! Reasonable rates, considerable portions and the employees are consistently friendly.
Glad they're back!
Very well organised and accessible place. They serve big meals and for reasonable rates. I enjoyed the menu very much and the staff members were super personal and chatty. Highly recommended.
One of the best fried chicken restaurants - tender meat and crunchy skin - while flavorful all the way through.  Other dishes are just okay.
This restaurant gives amazing service and tasty food. One of my favourite restaurants ever. The food came out rapidly and the prices are affordable. I recommend this place.
I visit this spot a lot since I work nearby. I love how their service is always great and they keep the spot well organized all the time. Prices are convenient and they serve sizeable portions.
I love this venue very much. It has a different spirit. The meals are great. the service is efficient and the waiters are polite. The price is modest. deeply recommend.
The soy garlic are my favorite wings in the city. The spicy are also very good but a bit too hot. I can't eat more than 5 or 6. The kimchi bacon fried rice is next level. Everything here is amazing.

Korean fried chicken is incredible in case you haven't tried it yet. The perfect amount of crunch without too much breading, and BonChon NAILS it. They also have a great selection of Korean/Korean inspired dishes in case you don't want fried chicken. The beer tower is a fun add on, and a good deal. Highly recommend.
(Translated by Google) Very good food  (Original) Muy buena comida
If you have not tried yet, try it.  You will love it.  I did.

I am just so over  “businesses” that are in locations they can’t survive in, and as a result, try making up for it by taking advantage of customers. I will NEVER go here again! I suggest you do the same and save yourself the utter disappointment and frustration. We took my mother and sister here for lunch. They have a lunch special which CLEARLY specifies on THEIR menu Mon - Friday 11:30 AM to 3 PM. We were sat at our table and the waitress came over a good 10-15 mins later and apologized for the wait, it was around 1:45 at this point. We began ordering from the lunch menu and then she stopped us and told us that this was over because the system had already changed 🤔 ..... Both my husband and I pointed to the time stated on the menu in frustration and the waitress began to argue with me about why it was over, clearly scamming. Her reasoning made no sense.  In addition to this, we ordered the bulgogi tacos which are promoted as having THREE tacos - we received 2 tacos filled with nothing but lettuce and two very tiny pieces of meat.  To conclude: this place is too pricy for the lackluster customer service and food! Do better, or please close (:

I had an interesting experience here. Came in for lunch and my first question was if they had wifi. I was told yes so I sat down and ordered. The short version is, no. No, they do not have wifi BUT my server got me the log in anyway. This is great service and I appreciated the access.  The lunch itself was fine. The food wasn't cheap ($13ish for 2 tacos and iced tea), but seemed high quality and fresh. The proportions in tacos were not ideal - way more lettuce and sauce than anything else. (Maybe that is how most Korean tacos are ?)  The space is cute and service is good, location is great. Overall, not bad.  If I went back, I would avoid the lunch specials menu and just order from the regular menu because the price cut isn't as significant as the portion cut.
I like Bonchon many times, but this is my first time in this branch, and it’s cool and the staff friendly
Love the chicken

Great Korean style fried chicken and other dishes. Friendly staff. Value is good, especially with the set meals. Service is quick. Great for when you don't have a lot of time but you don't want fast food.
Amazing chicken, love the soy garlic! Fast friendly service.

Chain restaurant with a bar and excellent Korean recipes. The spicy chicken bibimbop was delicious. The boneless fried chicken was also very good. The space has a comfortable clubby feel to it. The wait staff is friendly and helpful. Thanks for a great time!
Had really bad stomach flu after eating their fried chicken.
Super crisp chicken. A crunch in every bite. Potstickers are the best.

Awesome food, Chicken Bibimbap was spicy but delicious. The Bonchon wrap was also fantastic.  Also loved the steamed shrimp shumai.  Definitely want to come back to try their pork buns which look amazing, just didn’t have enough room to eat the entire menu today.  Next time!
Rat and bat meat.
Yum! Awesome Korean-style chicken. Huge portions in a fun, hip space. Just typing this review makes me want to go get some more. Highly recommend if you're in the mood for Korean fried chicken!

Sir,  This is in response to the review I left  some weeks ago (Lexi Castle) since I can not respond to your false accusations  You did not remove the Bibimbap from my meal nor give me a 15% discount. We came during the lunch special so it was slightly cheaper. Lets not LIE on the internet to make you look good. I ordered the Soy Chicken Bibimbap and the Fried Pickles for an appetizer. If you removed the Bimbimbap my bill would have came out to 6-7 dollars. I have the Screenshot of it not being taken off

The other day I found a piece of HAIR in my food. I told the waitress who then told her manager and he sounded very upset. They made me a new dish, the manager delivered it to me and didn’t even apologize for the HAIR in the food. Usually at any other high performance restaurant the meal would be comped or asked if there can be a complimentary add on for the inconvenience. Instead of making a fuss I paid for my meal and left. I am a frequent patron of this restaurant and I am very disappointed. The manager at this restaurant is very rude. This was not my first encounter with him being rude. Good luck to those who dine at this restaurant
So gooood! All the flavors are really good as are the fries.
Amazing wings!
Fried chicken is done pretty well. The chicken wings have a lot more skin to meat ratio. Drumsticks were large. I liked the sweet crunch flavor more than the soy garlic.
Seafood rice and octopus balls were amazing. The chicken is legit.
Too pricey for wings and not much variety of flavors.

This place is my preferable place.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to visit this restaurant. when  I feel like having a delicious supper, this restaurant comes immediately to my mind. outstanding and all sorts of  food and a rich menu.courteous crew, and great atmosphere. Also, the tariff is reasonable. I sent my friends to this place with no doubt.

LOVE the soy garlic wings and horseradish, paired with some white rice. Can’t get enough–I would eat there every week if I lived closer.  The Bucktown location is big. There’s lots of seating and a patio. They play dance music instead of the pop throwbacks at Chinatown. The staff was very friendly, professional and accommodating.  I always forget if I like the honey flavor and the server was nice enough to let me sample the sauces. I’m not a big fan but if sweet and honey are your thing, it’s worth a try.

Been here a few times. Everything I've tried tasted great, and their menu is quite extensive compared to other locations. The staff is courteous and pleasant, the place has a chill vibe and the food is just really worth coming back for.

Outstanding! Some of the best food I've had this year. It has some standard dishes with a Korean twist. The menu is not overly large but contains something for everyone. There were 7 of us and everybody ordered something different. The chicken was great. The wings, drumsticks and tenders were quite crispy on the outside but tender and juicy on the inside. The spicy sauce had a good kick to it. The Bonchon sauce was just a bit salty for me but had good flavor. One of the sides available is pickled daikon which I highly recommend. The soups were delicious with plenty of veggies. The ramen were fresh and silky. The marinated beef slice dishes were also excellent. The kimchee as a side was a great accompaniment. Prices were very reasonable. Service was quite quick even though they were busy. A fabulous place for lunch or dinner just west of Woodfield mall on Golf road (Illinois 58). Free parking and wheelchair accessible.
The chicken is predictably fantastic.  Service is efficient.  The ambiance is more upscale than the usual bonchon. Everything to love.  Nothing to dislike.
Their chicken is good but the portions are so small for the price that I can't recommend it over Crisp. Crisp is a far better value... Portions are larger and the chicken is much better.
The lychee soju is delicious!  The breading on the onion rings was perfectly crisp but not greasy.  The Korean tacos bulgogi are my wife's new favorite tacos

The food is delicious but the service from the staff was lacking. It took 20 minutes just to be served water. When the food was served, we weren’t given napkins and had to ask twice before some were provided. The most unfortunate part of the poor service was that it wasn’t even busy.
Good food and fast service.
Really good chicken strips!
Asian Fusion and Chicken at it's finest!!!
food couldn’t taste better, but a little on the pricey side
Smackin' on all levels. Great food, Beautiful decor, chill neighborhood. Great vibe for business, entertaining guests, or a first date.
A preferred site for tasty Korean food. I love visiting here. Service is consistently above par. This place has many great reviews for a reason.
korean food and the setting at this location is excellent. good place to catch up with friends. it has an awesome feel to it.

Ordered the plate of chicken strips, (careful when they say hot they really mean HOT!) delicious, not your regular thick flour coated strips. The fried zucchini was a nice change from fries. Great eats!!
HORRIBLE SERVICE!! THE OWNER "ROBERT"WAS THE RUDEST PERSON BY FAR I HAVE ENCOUNTERED. DO NOT GO HERE! SAVE YOUR MONEY!

HORRIBLE SERVICE BE AWARE!!!Worst welcoming experience I have ever endured. Not by the employees (They just stood there and glanced), but from the supposed owner"Robert"!!! DON'T GO THERE IF YOU DON'T WANT TO GET TALKED DOWN TO.

Was not impressed with this location. I eat Bonchons in Stapleton all the time and it is amazing. I spent $140 for food that tasted old. I told my friends how amazing  Bonchons was and all of us were left with a giant disappointment and plenty of wings left uneaten. My friends will not be returning!  However the waitress was very nice!
Aggressively average Korean food and mediocre service.

Wings seem smaller than the ones at Chinatown but the sauces are the same. Ordered the lunch special today. They didn’t give any radish, so I asked for some and when I paid I realize they charged me. In Chinatown when you order wings they give you free radish even if it’s a lunch special! If you’re craving Korean wings I would recommend going to the one in Chinatown instead, but if you can’t then this location is an inferior substitute.
Excellent food and great value for lunch.

that's not great that's not bad I stopped there for lunch I ordered the chicken combo that's worth spicy game that's why I hit was sweet actually which I am not crazy about and the temperature was lukewarm not as hot as it should be for fried chicken sandwich was good this is clean but the food the strip was so so I'll be back to check it out but I won't go out of my way to go in

This place is soooo GOOD! We had the wings both spicy and sweet, Kim chi and bacon fried rice, salmon avocado ball, and the seasoned fries! Everything was amazing!! The wings were crispy and the spicy ones were really spicy! The rice was to die for!!! The salmon was perfectly cooked and the fries was crispy on the outside and super soft on the inside! Highly recommend!

The food is fantastic if you're in the mood for great chicken. The overall ambiance is great, nice aesthetic going on. The staff was also very attentive and kind to the large group I was with. Definitely recommend.

These are some of my favorite wings to get. The recipe is true to the wings you get in Seoul. I have told several people about the chain, and they are hooked too. Glad it made its way to Chicago from the east coast!
If you want soggy garbage smelly food come here! The manager is very defensive. I only had a spoonful of it and paid and left. He didn’t want to change it.
Amazing chicken wings!
Little pricey but so yummy.and just like being in Busan.

Korean food is not even close to being one of my favorite types of food, but this place can fry a mean chicken. The strips take less time to cook, so if time is of the essence, try the boneless rather than the bone-in, but do try them. I ordered the japchae, my mum the bibimbap. We were both well pleased withour food although intolerances meant I had to remove some of my vegetables, and I would have liked a few more. The bibimbap was served in a sizzling crock that continued to sizzle and gave the rice a nice crispy crust on the bottom. The service was prompt and very courteous and I would not hesitate to go here again.
The food is excellent! Love the bibimbop!
Excellent food 👌👍👏

Great chicken. Skin crispy, meat tender and sauce on chicken flavorful. Ordered a medium order if chicken drumsticks today and took home to share. Did half sweet and half garlic soy. Could have done all 10 by myself. Saved some for tomorrow. Definitely will be back.

Poor operations. Every time I go here the waiters seem to lack training/attentiveness as you will constantly have to flag them down for service. They have also run out of basic staples like fries before. And Super Bowl Sunday, ordering apps said it would take 20-30min for an order but after not getting it, the restaurant they said it was a 2 hr wait for an order. They also disabled their phones so you couldn’t call to ask about an order.  Hoping Bon Chon Corporate can assist in improving this establishment as Bon Chon is such a great restaurant chain more generally.
I love their chicken. So flavorful and juicy!! Especially their drumsticks! This location is much bigger than the one in China town. Decor is nice, very clean and service was awesome.

Yummy we stopped in after theater in the area and were pleasantly surprised. Our server was very nice and our food was very tasty.  Shrimp shumai and bibimbap were great. We also really loved the salmon avocado. Will definitely return.
The chicken was very tasty and good but it was a little pricey but other than that it was good

username: Mad Science of Chicago's Western Suburbs

caption: Good food! Bibimbap was tasty. Mostly relaxed atmosphere - music was a little loud. Service was quick and friendly.

Really enjoyed the food here. Tons of flavor and spice. Solid drink list and trendy atmosphere. If you don't try the wings you're definitely missing out; there's something about that crispy, spicy, sweet kick that will have you reaching for more. 🤘🏾
The rudest and the worst customer service from the front desk guy ROBERT. I'll never visit the restaurant again.
Worst customer service Rude front desk guy Robert have to idea what he is doing. I'm a GrubHub driver I visit tons of restaurants everyday. I've never seen a worst service like this
Great wings, good dishes.  Their fried chicken is great.  Best consumed on premises but they also have takeout.
Service is good . But foods are wack

Amazing chicken!! Bonchon has lots of options. The seasoned fries are great and the bulgogi is very good. However, the bonchon chicken is to die for. It's crispy and glazy at the same time. The flavor is amazing and the texture makes it an experience. Definitely recommend both sweet and spicy flavors, you won't regret it

Great service and people. Very clean. Although I wish they would implement a happy hour of some sorts so it can be my new local go to bar. What's better than fried chicken and beer?... A deal on fried chicken and beer.

This is their second Chicago location. I was surprised to find that it is a bit less casual than the Chinatown location, but it makes sense knowing the neighborhood. I think the Chinatown location is a bit better. But it was still good. I like to order the chicken strips spicy and ginger soy. They do not have a lot of vegetarian options- but the steamed buns and chicken is good. They also do not serve dessert. This location does, however, serve alcohol. I would come here again because of convenience, but I would prefer to go to Chinatown because it is slightly better.
Overpriced and small portions. They also messed up my order.

Perfectly cooked delicious, crispy Korean Fried Chicken in the area. Definitely worth a view. The spicy level has a good kick, in a good way. The staff is nice. The service is good. The food is good. Portion sizes are pretty good too. Good lunch specials.
Love their Lunch Combo!
Tasty wings!
My favorite place to eat in the whole world. Try the soy garlic wings
The drumsticks were delicious and larger than expected. The spicy has enough spice to taste but not overpower the meal for people who like spice.
Nice place with great korean food.
Decent Korean fried chicken. Just wish they had an option for a sauce in between the sweet one and the very spicy one. Serving size was not very large and they were out of the boneless wings.
Everyone in my party got food poisoning after eating here. Would not recommend.

Fabulous food and drink as expected for bonchon chicken are good but lacking quantity on sauce coating chicken result in some what bland chicken. Understaff waiter make service really slow. Good fried and onion ring but that not really a main focus here.
Fully addicted to the soy garlic strips. Perfect combination of juicy and crispy chicken. The pork buns are amazing as well, great location and cool interior!!! I’d give it 6 stars if I could!!

I opted to pickup my order instead of sitting in. Initially, it took them a while to answer the phone. I finally got someone on my third call, who was a bit unpleasant. Her tone was off putting, but I disregarded it and proceeded to place my order.  Once I got there I was greeted by the same girl who I was on the phone with. She said very little and matched the energy she gave over the phone. Still, I ignored it and paid for my order. I ordered the combo chicken lunch special w/ fries and the house fried rice lunch special.  The price wasn’t bad for the amount of food I received, but the chicken could’ve used a lot more sauce then what was presented to me. Also, be sure to ask for condiments and silverware if needed. I had only two packets of ketchup in my bag and nothing else.  Prior to visiting this place I was on a Google search for Korean sticky chicken and this was one of the locations it suggested. Maybe I will try Crisp or Dak next time to see if I can actually get what I really want.  Overall, the food wasn’t bad, the price is doable, but the customer service could be better.
Mediocre and overpriced. Try Crisp or Del Seoul.
Very good great fried chicken

Soy garlic wings - 5/5. Spectacular. Spicy wings - 5/5. Too spicy for me, but my BiL says they're amazing; spicy but tasty, as opposed to Buffalo Wild Wings which try to be hot without flavor. Bibimbop - 5/5. Two of us ordered versions of this, and both were excellent.

Great spot for amazing Korean fried chicken. My previous favorite spot in the city was Crisp, but I think Bonchon is better!  The prices are reasonable, and they have a pretty large menu, but the fried chicken is a must!
My friend and I received food poisoning after eating here.

Food is amazing. The wings are a must try item. The spicy wings are flavorful and delicious. They definitely have a kick to them but not overbearingly spicy. The soy garlic wings are also excellent. They are flavorful but not too overbearing with the garlic. The pickled radishes are a great side companion. The seafood house fried rice is also great. It is delicious and has a good amount of seafood in it. The drink selection is pretty good as well; handful of options to choose from. The soju is delicious as well. We got the lychee and mango flavored soju and both were good, but I liked the lychee better. The service was excellent. Our server was friendly and welcoming and very attentive. The bathrooms are clean. The restaurant is clean and modern in decor. Street parking is ample. I would highly recommend this spot for grabbing dinner or late night eats.

Went for lunch on Friday - I couldn’t get over how quiet it was. As normal for any Bonchon location, the chicken was fantastic and they do a great lunch special. They currently have beers on the menu but no wine or liquor. The staff were pleasant and the space was clean.
Amazing food!! The chicken is cooked perfectly. Definitely drool-worthy.
Amazing fried chicken, the spicy hurts.  Also get the fried rice!
Happy this location is finally open.  So addictive.  Friendly service.  Top notch wings and mix of traditional Korean and Asian fusion. :)

I had lunch here off their lunch special menu.  Price seemed reasonable (under $10) for lunch and dinner portions around $12-$15.  Atmosphere and music were modern and enjoyable.  Servers were attentive and food came quickly and was delicious.  Their wings here are really good and perfectly cooked.  Had the tofu Bi Bim Bap bowl and it was good, the tofu was a little under seasoned but beside that this place is awesome.  I will defiantly be back for a casual lunch or dinner.

Sat at the bar. Clean good atmosphere and decoration - tv's for sports. But I waited 24 minutes after ordering to receive my chicken katsu. Others who were seated and ordered after me got their food before I did. It wasn't the servers fault - the woman acting as expediter didn't make my order a priority and maybe forgot to fire it. Rice was good. But plain. Chicken cutlet was a bit dry and not enough brown sauce. Not really special or worth going back to.  Restaurant was a third full and i waited more than 20 minutes for a flash fried chicken breast on rice.
Growing pains. I've had them try charging me for dinner prices for lunch items and the other time they just opened and couldn't serve food for an hour to change their oil. Not winning me over
Fried chicken took forever but was super good when it finally came!
Chicken is so crispy and delicious. Kim-chi and bacon fried rice and pork buns are great, too!

While the process to get a table was a bit disorganized, the food was absolutely delicious!!  We ordered a combo plate of chicken wings. Perfectly cooked with crispy skin, loads of eye-opening flavor, and tender meat. Certainly the best Korean Fried Chicken we've ever had. Medium size is more than enough to feed 2 people.  It has a pretty casual vibe inside with TVs in the bar area and a variety of seating options. Seems like a great spot for date night or small groups.  Definitely excited this place finally opened up after a long wait!
